<title>MEXICO: Segcoam Q1 net rises.</title>
<headline>Segcoam Q1 net rises.</headline>
<dateline>MONTERREY, Mexico 1997-04-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mexican insurer Seguros Comercial America (Segcoam) said its net profits were 75 million pesos in the first quarter, for a 26.5 percent increase from the first three months of 1996, the company said.</p>
<p>Revenue for the quarter was 2.345 billion pesos, a 10.9 percent increase from the year-ago period, the company said in a statement.  </p>
<p>Seguros Comercial America said in the quarter it began working with new affiliate Pensiones Comercial America.</p>
<p>((-- Daniel Perez-Whitaker, Monterrey bureau +528 3457617))</p>
